cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.MM, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on investigating the function of emotions in social media. It also involves the use of computational linguistics classifiers to analyze a large dataset of brand marketing messages from Google+ social networking site. 

It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the use of natural language processing techniques to compute the sentiment of the messages. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it explores the impact of emotions on word of mouth marketing and brand propagation, which has implications for society and consumer behavior. 

It may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as social media often involves the use of multimedia content such as images and videos, which can also evoke emotions. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it involves the development and application of computational models to analyze social media data.
